# Dockerfile

```Dockerfile
FROM registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8/ubi:8.10

USER root

# Install required packages
RUN dnf install -y \
    python3 \
    python3-pip \
    sudo \
    openssh-clients \
    sshpass \
    git \
    vim \
    iputils \
    hostname \
    which \
    tar \
    shadow-utils \
    sssd-client \
    krb5-workstation \
    authselect \
    && dnf clean all

# Upgrade pip
RUN python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip

# Install Ansible and networking libraries
RUN pip3 install \
    ansible==9.* \
    ansible-pylibssh \
    paramiko \
    netmiko \
    jmespath \
    dnspython

# Install Cisco collections
RUN ansible-galaxy collection install \
    cisco.ios \
    cisco.nxos \
    cisco.asa \
    ansible.netcommon

# Create automation group
RUN groupadd automation

# Disable root password login
RUN passwd -l root

# Create workspace
RUN mkdir -p /ansible

# Set permissions
RUN chgrp -R automation /ansible && \
    chmod -R 2775 /ansible

WORKDIR /ansible

CMD ["/bin/bash"]
```

# Build Image

```bash
docker build -t rhel8-ansible-cisco .
```

# Run Container with Active Directory Integration

```bash
docker run -it \
  --name ansible-cisco \
  --network host \
  -v $(pwd):/ansible \
  -v /etc/passwd:/etc/passwd:ro \
  -v /etc/group:/etc/group:ro \
  -v /etc/shadow:/etc/shadow:ro \
  -v /etc/sssd:/etc/sssd:ro \
  -v /var/lib/sss:/var/lib/sss:ro \
  -v /etc/krb5.conf:/etc/krb5.conf:ro \
  --user $(id -u):$(id -g) \
  rhel8-ansible-cisco
```

# Verify Active Directory User

Inside container:

```bash
whoami
id
```

Expected:

* Your AD username
* Your AD UNIX groups
* No root access

# Verify Ansible

```bash
ansible --version
```

# Verify Cisco Collections

```bash
ansible-galaxy collection list
```

# Verify Group Membership

```bash
groups
```

Expected:

* automation
* domain groups
* linux groups

# Notes

This container:

* does not run as root
* uses host AD authentication
* supports enterprise UNIX identity management
* allows centralized RBAC using AD groups
* works well for shared automation teams

# Recommended Host Configuration

The Linux host should already be joined to Active Directory using:

```bash
realm join DOMAIN.LOCAL
```

Verify:

```bash
id your_ad_user
```

before starting the container.
